-- Beijing Bank, Rural Commercial, Guangfa Bank: China Bond Alert
-- B y   R a c h e l   E v a n s
-- 2012-12-25T03:19:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-25/beijing-bank-rural-commercial-guangfa-bank-china-bond-alert.html
Bank of Beijing Co., Beijing Rural
Commercial Bank Co.,  China  Guangfa Bank Co., China Merchants
Bank Co. and Bank of Tianjin Co. are among issuers that may sell
bonds in the nation’s debt markets.  Domestic Bonds  BANK OF BEIJING CO.: The bank has won approval from
People’s Bank of China to sell up to 30 billion yuan ($4.8
billion) of debt on the nation’s interbank market, according to
a statement to Shanghai’s stock exchange. (Added Dec. 25)  BEIJING RURAL COMMERCIAL BANK CO.: The bank plans to sell
as much as 5.1 billion yuan of 10-year subordinated bonds on
Dec. 27, according to a statement posted to Chinabond.com.cn,
the Chinese government bond clearing house website. (Added Dec.
25)  CHINA GUANGFA BANK CO.: The bank plans to sell 2 billion
 yuan  of 10-year and 2.5 billion yuan of 15-year bonds on Dec.
27, according to a statement posted to Chinabond.com.cn, the
Chinese government bond clearing house website. (Added Dec. 25)  CHINA MERCHANTS BANK CO.: The bank plans to sell up to 6
billion yuan of 10-year subordinated bonds and up to 5.7 billion
yuan of 15-year bonds on Dec. 27, according to a statement
posted to Chinamoney.com.cn, a website of the China Foreign
Exchange Trade System. (Added Dec. 25)  BANK OF TIANJIN CO.: The bank plans to sell as much as 1.35
billion yuan of 10-year and 1.35 billion yuan of 15-year
subordinated bonds on Dec. 27, according to a statement posted
to Chinamoney.com.cn, a website of the China Foreign Exchange
Trade System. (Added Dec. 25)  SANYA PHOENIX INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT CO.: The company plans
to sell 500 million yuan of one-year bonds on the  interbank
market , according to data compiled by Bloomberg. The notes will
settle on Dec. 28, the data show. (Added Dec. 25)  CHENGDU COMMUNICATION INVESTMENT GROUP CO.: The company
plans to sell 1 billion yuan of five-year bonds today. (Updated
Dec. 25)  SHANGHAI PUDONG DEVELOPMENT BANK CO.: The bank plans to
sell up to 12 billion yuan of 15-year subordinated bonds on Dec.
27, according to a statement posted to Chinamoney.com.cn, a
website of the China Foreign Exchange Trade System. (Added Dec.
24)  ELION RESOURCES GROUP CO.: The company plans to sell 1.2
billion yuan of one-year bonds on Dec. 27, according to data
compiled by Bloomberg. (Added Dec. 21)  PING AN INSURANCE (GROUP) CO.: The company’s board renewed
a mandate for the sale of 26 billion yuan of convertible bonds,
according to a statement posted to  Shanghai  Stock Exchange.
(Added Dec. 19)  CHINA EASTERN AIRLINES CORP.: The company obtained
regulatory approval for up to 8.8 billion yuan of bond issuance,
according to a statement to the Shanghai Stock Exchange. (Added
Dec. 17)  FUFENG GROUP LTD.: The company obtained a regulatory
approval to issue up to 1.2 billion yuan of medium-term notes
for its subsidiary Neimenggu Fufeng Biotechnologies Co.,
according to a statement posted on Hong Kong Stock Exchange.
(Added Dec. 17)  HEBEI IRON & STEEL CO.: The company won a regulatory
approval to issue up to 5 billion yuan of bonds, according to a
statement posted to the Shenzhen Stock Exchange. (Added Dec. 17)  DATONG COAL INDUSTRY CO.: The company plans to sell 3
billion yuan in medium-term notes with a maturity of no more
than five years, according to a statement to the  Shanghai Stock
Exchange . (Added Dec. 11)  HUAIBEI CITY CONSTRUCTION INVESTMENT & DEVELOPMENT CO.: The
company has approval to sell as much as 1.8 billion yuan of six-
year bonds, according to a statement from the National
Development and Reform Commission in Anhui province. (Added Dec.
11)  DATANG INTERNATIONAL POWER GENERATION CO.: The company won
approval to sell 6 billion yuan of bonds, according to a
statement posted to Shanghai Stock Exchange. (Added Dec. 10)  CHONGQING CITY: The western city of China plans to sell
bonds to finance small and medium-sized companies in the region,
the official Xinhua News Agency reported, without citing anyone.
Chongqing plans to sell 350 million yuan of bonds to raise funds
for five companies, the report said. (Added Dec. 6)  SHANGHAI ELECTRIC GROUP CO.: The company won approval for
its 4 billion yuan bond issuance, according to a statement
posted to Shanghai Stock Exchange. (Added Dec. 6)  SHANDONG CHENMING PAPER HOLDINGS LTD.: The manufacturer won
approval from China Securities Regulatory Commission for its 3.8
billion yuan bond sale, according to a statement posted to
Shenzhen Stock Exchange. (Added Dec. 6)  AIR CHINA LTD.: The company won approval from China
Securities Regulatory Commission to sell as much as 10 billion
yuan of bonds, according to a statement posted to the Shanghai
Stock Exchange. (Added Nov. 30)  CHINA YANGTZE POWER CO.: The company plans to sell 2
billion yuan of one-year bonds, according to a statement posted
to Shanghai Clearing House’s website. (Updated Nov. 29)  Dim Sum Bonds  BRITISH COLUMBIA: The Canadian province hired HSBC Holdings
Plc to arrange bond investor meetings, according to a person
familiar with the matter. (Updated Dec. 13)  To contact the reporter on this story:
